<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-03T22:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-03T22:29:00-05:00" n="558" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d558">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1376</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-03T22:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1917, 10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your June 2, 4 p.m. Having expressed himself as reported in my May 16, 11
                            p.m. replying to Department’s offer May 15, 3 p.m. President said
                            nothing to announcement in Department’s May 18, 4 p.m. that troops would
                            be sent to Guantanamo station except to repeat there would be no
                            occasion call upon their services. He expected to relieve with regular
                            troops all marines then guarding property. Conditions have improved
                            daily since inauguration of the President and nothing to indicate
                            Government needs assistance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>